My role. Project Recovery for a Stalled IT Project

Project description.

I was invited as a Project Recovery / Business Analysis consultant to help a stalled IT project that was over budget and behind schedule. I analysed the situation, clarified scope and processes, and worked with the team to stabilise delivery.
Skills and deliverables

Project Planning
Project Delivery
Published on Jan 2, 2026
Client & context

A company had an ongoing IT project that was significantly delayed, with unclear scope and constant changes. The management needed a realistic recovery plan and better control over the project.
Problem

Requirements were not clearly documented, priorities constantly shifted, and communication between business and the development team was fragmented. As a result, the project burned time and budget without delivering stable value.
My role

Project Recovery Consultant & Business Analyst brought in to assess the situation and help bring the project back on track.
What I did

- reviewed existing documentation, backlog and current implementation status
- conducted interviews with stakeholders to understand goals, expectations and constraints
- clarified and restructured requirements into a clear, prioritised backlog
- mapped key business processes to identify gaps, bottlenecks and risks
- proposed a realistic recovery plan with phases, milestones and scope boundaries
- facilitated communication between business and development to ensure alignment going forward
Result

- reduced scope ambiguity and aligned stakeholders around a clear plan
- stabilised the project and enabled the team to deliver a focused, valuable release
- improved transparency of budget, timelines and process for management